Package gw.api.path

Interface Path<A,B>

Type Parameters:
A - Root type of the path.
B - Leaf type of the path.
All Known Implementing Classes:
PersistentPath
public interface Path<A,B>
A path of PropertyReferences. The first property reference must have owner type <A> and the last property reference must have feature type <B>. Additionally, every path element must have an owner type that is either the same type as or a subtype of the feature type of the previous element in the path.

Paths can be constructed as follows: 

Paths.make(InvoiceItem#Invoice, AccountInvoice#Account)
